covered: Valid Request: Scenarios cover successful retrieval with default params, offset/limit, and audit variations.
Empty Response: Scenarios for no bundles and partially populated databases exist.
Query Parameters: Extensive coverage of valid and invalid parameters (offset, limit, audit) and edge cases (extra params, SQL injection attempt, negative values, max values).
Pagination: Several scenarios cover basic pagination and boundary conditions (TC01, TC02, TC07, TC21).
Error Handling: Tests for invalid parameters (TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11, TC14), and dependency failure/timeout (TC13, TC22).
Performance: Basic and peak load tests (TC17, TC18).
Regression: Backward compatibility and prior-audit behavior (TC19, TC20).
gaps: Pagination: Limited explicit coverage for large dataset pagination correctness beyond basic offset/limit (e.g., ensuring stable ordering across pages).
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache validation.
Rate Limiting: No explicit tests for rate limiting/throttling behavior beyond performance/scaling scenarios.
Authorization Nuances: While TC12 covers unauthorized, no explicit coverage for forbidden (403) on authenticated but insufficient permissions.
Timeout/Resilience Granularity: Only a single timeout/503 scenario (TC22) without diversified timeout/retry behavior tests.
Edge Case: Very large offset/limit with non-integer types or malformed inputs beyond provided invalid cases.
recommendations: Add tests to verify caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache invalidation behavior.
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure proper handling under bursts and repeated requests.
Add a 403 Forbidden scenario to cover authenticated users lacking required permissions.
Enhance pagination tests with more rigorous large-dataset paging checks (ordering consistency across pages).
Add more resilience tests around timeouts with retries and fallback behavior.
